OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be cloudy in the
OL,6,Fmorning with rain for a time. Drier
OL,7,Fwith some brighter spells developing
OL,8,Fin the afternoon, but still the chance
OL,9,Fof the odd shower. Warm.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FSome brightness to start but
OL,12,Frain soon spreading north through the
OL,13,Fevening. This clearing before midnight
OL,14,Fto leave a dry night with some clear
OL,15,Fspells developing.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FWarm again. A quite cloudy
OL,18,Fmorning with patchy drizzle in the
OL,19,Fwest.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
